subSubSection.paragraph:
Soil.
The soil is classified as Dystrophic Red Argisols, but mixed with Dystrophic Red-Yellow Argisols (

Santos 
et al.
2011

). These 
types
of soils have accentuated red colors due to higher levels of iron oxides and usually occur in areas of undulating relief, but they can be identified in less steep areas. They have low fertility that could be explained by relief slope, nutrient limitations, strong acidity, high drainage capacity and also high susceptibility to erosion and degradation (AGEITEC 2021a; 

Santos 
et al.
2011

; 
2021a
; 
2021b
; 

Streck 
et al.
2002

; 
2008
).
